WEBVTT

00:00:00.271 --> 00:00:04.355
Responses to challenges are heavily dictated by personal values.

00:00:05.016 --> 00:00:11.642
Values are individually internalized attitudes about what is right, wrong, ethical, and moral.

00:00:12.383 --> 00:00:15.986
They heavily influence perceptions of problems and preferences.

00:00:16.807 --> 00:00:23.895
Challenges often lack simplistic answers, and an internal code of ethics determines how power is exercised.

00:00:24.476 --> 00:00:27.420
The congruence gravity model explains this simply.

00:00:28.060 --> 00:00:29.422
First, you have values.

00:00:30.043 --> 00:00:31.665
Second, you have beliefs.

00:00:32.285 --> 00:00:34.107
Third, you have actions.

00:00:35.036 --> 00:00:42.300
When thoughts, feelings, and behaviors align with genuineness and honesty towards others, congruence is achieved.

00:00:42.840 --> 00:00:49.343
Congruence grounds leadership in values, provides stability for the team, allows others to predict actions,

00:00:49.764 --> 00:00:52.065
and fundamentally builds shared trust.
